<!-- This here is the code for breaking down vanilla Power Armors and Helmets.
You get as much materials as you need to craft them. This can allow you to either modularize them via my Modular Power Armor sets...
...Or just simply recraft them. It fixes the damage, it rerolls the quality. No resource loss.
Unbalanced? Not too much. You need to finish a lengthy research for it, it needs lots of time so it's more like an opportunity cost.
You have to commit time you could use for other things. That's good enough of a price in my opinion.

You can also "recalibrate" the Mark V Modular Power Armor pieces. This one takes some resources and fixes the health of the items.
It was designed for people not using any mending mods, to not feel cheated after their extremely-expensive-to-make Mark V gets too damaged.
I *could* add recalibration for the lower tiers too but that would clutter the Component Assembly Bench's crafting list even more. -->
<!-- Obligatory honorary mention to Ykara, creator of the well-known EPOE mod. I had this mod of mine for personal use since A12...
...And back then I used EPOE's code of unlocking a recipe and assigning it to an existing workstation with research via DLL.
I've asked Ykara back then if I can use the code and she granted permission, while also stating that it's not necessary.
Indeed, it wasn't necessary at all and I haven't used the DLL since A12. Still, this pushed me to make my first DLL mod.
Mostly with code I stol- I mean borrowed from EPOE. With permission. So yeah, it's really not stealing in this case. -->
